<subSubSection type="etymology">
<paragraph pageNumber="761">
Etymology L Gr 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:182082" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole subsphaerica Wilson" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole subsphaerica Wilson" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="761" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="subsphaerica">subsphaerica</taxonomicName>
, shaped somewhat like a ball, referring to the head of the major.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageNumber="761">
Diagnosis A large, unusual species of the 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:34070" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole tristis (Smith)" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole tristis (Smith)" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="761" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tristis">tristis</taxonomicName>
group, similar to 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:182062" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole pepo Wilson" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole pepo Wilson" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="761" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pepo">pepo</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:182072" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole rotundiceps Wilson" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole rotundiceps Wilson" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="761" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rotundiceps">rotundiceps</taxonomicName>
, and the dramatically unique 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:182081" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole sphaerica Wilson" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole sphaerica Wilson" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="761" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sphaerica">sphaerica</taxonomicName>
(q.v.), and distinguished as follows.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="description">
<paragraph pageNumber="761">Major: head in full-face view circular, with flattened posterior dorsal margin; carinulae limited to the level of the posterior margin of the eye, those originating mesad to the eye curving downward below the eye and then back up again, as illustrated; promesonotum and head mostly smooth and shiny; postpetiole cone-shaped; all of body densely pilose.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageNumber="761">Measurements (mm) Holotype major: HW 2.02, HL 1.94, SL 1.18, EL 0.26, PW 0.94.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageNumber="761">Paratype minor: HW 0.66, HL 0.42, SL 0.96, EL 0.14, PW 0.44.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageNumber="761">Color Major: concolorous light reddish yellow.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageNumber="761">Minor: concolorous clear yellow.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="distribution">
<paragraph pageNumber="761">range Known only from the type locality.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
